additional comments for web: The district said it only offers middle school students sensitvity training if a transgender student is enrolled at the school. Such training is not provided to elementary school students.
The district, along with at least 4 others in the Bay Area, does not provide teachers training on transgender issues.  The district declined an on-camera interview.
The district said it provides annual staff and teacher training sessions that include a review of the district's non-discrimination policy.
This year, the district held it's first-ever training session for teachers after only providing such training to school administrators.
The district estimates 60-65 transgender students are enrolled in the district.

The district said it is open to potentially providing teacher training specific to transgender issues. In the meantime, it said it focuses on a "personalized approach" to tend to the needs of each student who identifies as transgender.
The district, along with at least 4 others in the Bay Area, does not provide teachers training on transgender issues. The district declined an on-camera interview.
All middle and high schools at the district have an on-site LGBTQ liason, who is the point person for LGBTQ youth.
The district contracts with Gender Spectrum to educate teachers on gender issues.
The district contracts with Gender Spectrum and Our Space to educate teachers on gender issues.

The district said it also provides training for school nurses and parents. The district estimates it has approximately 200 transgender students: 50 in elementary school, 50 in middle school, and 150 in high school.
The district declined an on-camera interview, but said it provides teachers "robust training" on issues related to gender and race.
The district said it works with Adolescent Counseling Services to provide gender education to students at all 4 of its middle schools.
Beginning this year, students in the district can provide a preferred name and pronoun (gender marker). Only legal documents, such as a diploma, will include the student's legal name.
